This example illustrates the communication of rome and argus.

You can start the program either in one process with an analyzer
running together with a display or in two separate processes
communication over sockets.

One Process:
------------

Start the program with :
  singleProcessConfig.xml

Two Processes :
---------------

Start the program with :
  separateProcessConfigAnalyzer.xml
  and choose '0' in the separateProcessConfigAnalyzer.xml under <ProgramConfiguration> - <ProgramMode>
  or choose 'Analyzer' in the config GUI under 'RunMode'

Start the program again with :
  separateProcessConfigMonitor.xml
  and choose '3' in the separateProcessConfigMonitor.xml under <ProgramConfiguration> - <ProgramMode>
  or choose 'Monitor connecting to Analyzer' in the config GUI under 'RunMode'


